The paper discusses graph embedding techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining applications. The focus is on improving scalability and non-linearity, which are important considerations in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
